views.text: Sleep quality score is based on the Pittsburgh Sleep Quality Index calculation. Basic principles are measured through the device like the regularity of sleep, sleep duration, deep sleep ratio, time awake during the night, wake up time and other factors to assess sleep quality and score.
Sleep efficiency reflects the percentage of time spent asleep compared to time spent awake while in bed. More than 85% is a sign of good sleep.
Optimally, the midpoint of your night's sleep should fall between midnight and 3 AM.

The sleep heart rate curve shows three different sleep heart rate patterns, which can be used as a basis to judge the quality of sleep and the degree of recovery from rest, showing the characteristics of your heart.
The temperature difference is calculatedby comparing it to your average temperature.

Temperature variations can reveal a lot about your recovery and overall health. Compared with daytime, the body is in its most stable state during sleep time. Device and shows your average temperature relative to your baseline. We advise users to keep an eye out for any fluctuation greater than 0.5°C / 0.90 °F, ineither a positive or negative direction.
